Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportTwoPinChain(25.10)                              reportTwoPinChain(25.10)

Name
       reportTwoPinChain

Syntax
       reportTwoPinChain

       [-help]

       [-reset  |

       [[-output <fileName>] [-through <string>]

       [-noOverwrite ]

       [-showAll ]

       [-strict ]

       [-tolerance <value>]]]

       Reports  two  pin chains for nets, instterms, and hinstterms. This com-
       mand can traverse through buffers, inverters, and assign-statements and
       report the complete two pin chain. You can specify any element  of  the
       chain  to  get  the same results. The reportTwoPinChain command is used
       after pin assignment to analyse results and debug issues especially  in
       cases  where  the expectation to align all partition pins across a two-
       pin chain is not met.

Parameter
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each reportTwoPinChain parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportTwoPinChain

       -noOverwrite
              When  specified  the  report  continues  to display the previous
              2-pin-chains also.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -output <fileName>
              Specifies the file in  which  the  2-pin  nets  are  traced  and
              dumped.

              Default: stdout

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reset Removes GUI markers and GUI objects, created during previous in-
              vocations. No two pin chain reporting.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -showAll
              Displays the intermediate instances of the chain also.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -strict
              Strictly  displays  only pure two pin chains even at module port
              connections.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -through <string>
              Specifies the list of names of net,  instterms,  hinstterms  for
              which 2-pin chains are traced and dumped.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -tolerance <value>
              Specifies  the tolerance range. This specified difference in or-
              dinates treated as still aligned.

              Default: 1.0 microns

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * In the following diagram P1, P2, W3/P3 are partitions  and  W3
                is a non-partition verilog module.

                It  shows  a  pure two pin connection where red and green pins
                aligned together in one chain.

                The following command  reports  this  two  pin  chain  passing
                through p2/I1/Y:

                reportTwoPinChain -through p2/I1/Y

              * The  following  command  reports  the  two  pin chains passing
                through DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/port_pad_data_out[13]:

                reportTwoPinChain                                     -through
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/port_pad_data_out[13]

                Report:

                2-pin-chain                                           through:
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/port_pad_data_out[13] ...

                 chain terminator: other pin of buffer is multi-fanout

                 net: DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/port_data_in[13]

                 buffer-term                      :output    :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/TDSP_CORE_GLUE_INST/i_9686/Y

                 module-port                      :output    :unplaced       :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/TDSP_CORE_GLUE_INST/port_data_in[13]

                 module-port                      :input     :unplaced       :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/data_in[13]

                 buffer-term                      :input     :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/FE_RC_7_0/A

                 net: DTMF_INST/FE_FEEDX_NET_D__tdsp_core__0_tdsp_portO_13_

                 buffer-term                      :output    :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/FE_RC_7_0/Y

                 module-port                      :output    :unplaced       :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/pad_data_out[13]

                 partition-pin                    :output    :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/port_pad_data_out[13]

                 partition-pin                    :input     :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/RE-
                SULTS_CONV_INST/FE_FEEDX_NET_D__tdsp_core__0_tdsp_portO_13_

                 buffer-term                      :input     :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/RE-
                SULTS_CONV_INST/FE_OFC28_FE_FEEDX_NET_D__tdsp_core__0_tdsp_portO_13_/A

                 net: tdsp_portO[13]

                 buffer-term                      :output    :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/RE-
                SULTS_CONV_INST/FE_OFC28_FE_FEEDX_NET_D__tdsp_core__0_tdsp_portO_13_/Y

                 partition-pin                    :output    :placed         :
                DTMF_INST/RESULTS_CONV_INST/FE_FEEDX_P_tdsp_portO_13_

                 module-port                      :output    :unplaced       :
                DTMF_INST/port_pad_data_out[13]

                 module-port                      :input     :unplaced       :
                IOPADS_INST/tdsp_portO[13]

                 buffer-term                      :input     :placed         :
                IOPADS_INST/Ptdspop13/I

                 net: port_pad_data_out[13]

                 buffer-term                      :output    :placed         :
                IOPADS_INST/Ptdspop13/PAD

                 module-port                      :output    :unplaced       :
                IOPADS_INST/tdsp_port_out[13]

                 chip-io                          :output    :fixed          :
                port_pad_data_out[13]

                 chain terminator: chip-io

              * The  following  command  reports  the  two  pin chains passing
                through F2/D2/A/out and writes it to report.txt file:

                reportTwoPinChain -through F2/D2/A/out -output report.txt

